item.title: Alcohol Consuming Analysis
item.description: Back in 2014, fivethiryeight.com published an article on alchohol consumption in different countries. The data drinks is available as part of the fivethirtyeight package. Let’s get the data. library(fivethirtyeight) data(drinks) Before further analysis, let’s have a brief look into the dataframe. glimpse(drinks) ## Rows: 193 ## Columns: 5 ## $ country <chr> "Afghanistan", "Albania", "Algeria", "A… ## $ beer_servings <int> 0, 89, 25, 245, 217, 102, 193, 21, 261,… ## $ spirit_servings <int> 0, 132, 0, 138, 57, 128, 25, 179, 72, 7… ## $ wine_servings <int> 0, 54, 14, 312, 45, 45, 221, 11, 212, 1… ## $ total_litres_of_pure_alcohol <dbl> 0.
